rmat=\"true\" Name=\"Intense Reference\"/>rn  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"33\" SemiHidden=\"false\"rn   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Book Title\"/>rn  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"37\" Name=\"Bibliography\"/>rn  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"39\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"TOC Heading\"/>rn </w:LatentStyles>rn</xml><![endif]--><!-- [if gte mso 10]>rn<style>rn /* Style Definitions */rn table.MsoNormalTablern	{mso-style-name:\"Table Normal\";rn	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;rn	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;rn	mso-style-noshow:yes;rn	mso-style-priority:99;rn	mso-style-qformat:yes;rn	mso-style-parent:\"\";rn	mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;rn	mso-para-margin:0in;rn	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;rn	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;rn	font-size:11.0pt;rn	font-family:\"Cambria\",\"serif\";rn	mso-ascii-font-family:Cambria;rn	mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;rn	mso-hansi-font-family:Cambria;rn	mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;}rn</style>rn<![endif]-->','residential'),(6,'images/project6.jpg','Makeen Tower','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Artica Interiors was appointed to design and build an office space in the prestigious Makeen Tower in Abu Dhabi. The design brief was to create a functional office with lots of open spaces to give a very expansive feeling. The overall design was conceptualised on contemporary lines reflecting an European styled office. The signature element in the design was the concealed storage system integrated with the very sleek finish. The interiors blended well with the design seamlessly and whole office space was harmoniously functional.</p>','commercial'),(7,'images/project7.jpg','Orchestra','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Artica was commissioned to fit-out this fine dining restaurant in the Dubai Festival City which was concept designed by a famous Lebanese restaurant designer Bureau Antoine Tabet. Artica had thus embarked on developing the detailed working drawings, selection of materials, custom making many of the design features. All the lighting chandeliers, lighted mashrabia patterns, and furniture were custom made keeping the original design intent intact. The overall project was thoroughly planned and executed to the minute detail resulting in a very signature restaurant.</p>','hospitality'),(10,'images/project10.jpg','Choco Bar','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;Artica was commissioned to fit-out the Chocolate Bar restaurant in the Mirdif City Centre of Dubai. This is a franchise American restaurant designed locally by HDD Interiors. Artica had worked on the construction details and executed the project in line with the requirements of the client. The overall project was delivered with the exceptional quality material finishes blending seamless between soft and hard finishing resulting in a masterpiece hideout for a quality time out.</p>','hospitality'),(11,'images/project11.jpg','Al Jaber Gallery','<p>Al Jaber Gallery</p>','retail'),(12,'images/project12.jpg','Mirdiff Villa','<p>Private villa renovation. The work was centered around creating a very upscale living space. We worked on multiple room concepts while keeping the common areas of the villa uniform.The focus on the renovation was to cater to the new and evolving family demands and requirements.</p>\r\n<p>The overall work required a very thorough analysis in order to solve the functionality and utility of the villa space. Furthermore, we worked on solving all related technical issues.</p>\r\n<p><!-- [if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n  <o:AllowPNG/>\r\n </o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n</xml><![endif]--></p>','residential'),(13,'images/project13.jpg','Mark Inn Hotel','<p>Artica Interiors was appointed to fully refurbish Mark Inn hotel which included the hotel facade, all the rooms and public areas. Public areas such as the reception and restaurants were upgraded and kept in line with the overall hotel look, creating a warm atmosphere and using desert tone colours.</p>\r\n<p>Before the refurbishment, the hotel had only a one room category. However, in order to cater to various guest and budgets, we came up with the concept of a four suite configuration.</p>\r\n<p>Furthermore, great emphasis were put on space planning in order to achieve the most functional and feasible solution which would enhance the overall hotels operations.</p>','hospitality'),(14,'images/project14.jpg','Khalifa Fund Office - Al Ain','<p>After Artica Interiors successfully completing three offices for Khalifa Fund, Artica continued to be blessed with the support from Khalifa Fund for Enterprise Development and appointed to design their forth office in Al Ain.</p>\r\n<p>We were very proud to win the design / build competition which was submitted via a tender.</p>\r\n<p>Al Ain office is the largest space of all the four Khalifa Fund projects Artica completed.</p>\r\n<p>The previous designs centered around a contemporary look whereas this project was to channel a much more fresh and youthful design with the emphasis on lighter colours and materials.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','commercial');
